Go to Desktop → Right-click → New → Folder → Name it git_tag_release.
Open Git Bash.
git init
ls -a
touch main.py
echo "This is the first version of the file." > main.py
git add main.py
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git log --oneline
Create a repository on GitHub → Name: Git_Tag_Release → Public → Add README.md → Create Repository.
git remote add origin https://github.com/Shreya281105/Git_Tag_Release.git
git push -u origin main
git pull origin main
git tag v1.0
git tag -a v1.2 -m "v1.2 Created"
git tag
git show v1.0
git push origin v1.0
git push --tags
git tag v2.0
git push origin v2.0
git tag -l
git tag -l "v1.*"
git tag -d v1.0
git push origin -d v1.0
Open GitHub → Your repository → Click Releases → Draft a new release
Select tag: v1.0 (or whichever tag you want to release)Add release title → Add notes (optional) Click Publish release
git fetch --tags
git tag
git show v2.0
